# TODO: black-brown coalition


@popular_front_coalition
title: A new "Popular Front" coalition?
subtitle: <span style="color: #ac2639;">**SPD**</span> + <span style="color: #db7097;">**USPD**</span> + <span style="color: #c66cda;">**RDP**</span> + <span style="color: #000;">**Z**</span> ([+ popular_front_coalition +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: <span style="color: #ac2639;">**SPD**</span> + <span style="color: #db7097;">**USPD**</span> + <span style="color: #c66cda;">**RDP**</span> + <span style="color: #000;">**Z**</span> ([+ popular_front_coalition +]%) - [? if ((spd_relation < 65 and spd_ideology == "Centre") or (spd_relation < 45 and spd_ideology == "Right")): We do not have good enough relations with the <span style="color: #ac2639;">SPD</span>. ?] [? if spd_ideology == "Left": The <span style="color: #ac2639;">**SPD**</span> is too radical to tame. ?] [? if spd_coalition < 4 : The <span style="color: #ac2639;">Social Democrats</span> are unwilling to participate in a bourgeois government. ?] [? if clerical_strength + labour_strength >= left_strength : Our party is not left-wing enough. ?]
view-if: popular_front_coalition >= 50
choose-if: (((spd_relation >= 65 and spd_ideology == "Centre") or (spd_relation >= 45 and spd_ideology == "Right")) and (spd_ideology == "Centre" or spd_ideology == "Right") and spd_coalition >= 3 and (left_strength >= clerical_strength + labour_strength))

Following in the footsteps of our Badenese branch, we have formed a coalition with the SPD. This move is expected to be highly controversial among our party and theirs, and compromise will be key.

The far-right might attempt a coup, if such a coalition were formed.

- @great_popular_front: Form the Popular Front!
- @coalition_menu: This is inadvisable. Try another governing arrangement.

@great_popular_front
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 1; uspd_in_government = 1; rdp_in_government = 1; z_in_government = 1; in_popular_front = 1; chancellor = "Müller"; chancellor_party = "USPD"; spd_relation += 10; coup_progress += 2 if spd_ideology == "Centre"; in_left_front = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; spd_dissent = 1; uspd_dissent = 0; rdp_dissent = 0;

achievement: grosse_volksfront
go-to: popular_front_civil_war if coup_progress >= 10; popular_front_no_civil_war if coup_progress < 10

Hermann Müller of the USPD is selected by the negotiating committee as Chancellor. 

@popular_front_success
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 1; in_popular_front = 1; chancellor = "Breitscheid"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; kpd_relation += 10; coup_progress += 2; in_left_front = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; coalition_dissent = 0;
go-to: popular_front_civil_war if coup_progress >= 10; popular_front_no_civil_war if coup_progress < 10
achievement: volksfront

Somehow, surprisingly, the coalition is successfully formed! We still need a chancellor; the only acceptable choice among the parties was Rudolf Breitscheid of the SPD, acceptable to the Center and KPD [? if president == "Hindenburg" : as well as President Hindenburg, albeit extremely reluctantly ?].

@popular_front_no_civil_war
on-arrival: spd_goals_seen = 0; finance_minister_party = "USPD"; interior_minister_party = "Z"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; foreign_minister_party = "RDP"; agriculture_minister_party = "USPD"; reichswehr_minister = "Z"; leverage = z_r;
achievement: volksfront

In response to the KPD's entrance into the government, the right-wing takes a "wait-and-see" approach for now. They expect that the Popular Front government will be unstable and incompetent, and will collapse of its own accord, discrediting the left and center and eventually enabling the destruction of the Weimar Republic. Our task is to prove them wrong.

The KPD has taken an abstentionist position with regards to ministries. They claim to be participating as the "loyal opposition" within the Popular Front government, supporting us from the outside while also running their own propaganda campaigns to turn workers to their side. They seem to expect that the Popular Front would inevitably fail, and that our failure would benefit them.

- @ministries: First, we must select our ministries.


@popular_front_civil_war
on-arrival: spd_relation = 80; uspd_relation = 80; rdp_relation = 80; reichswehr_loyalty += 0.25;

In response to the SPD's entrance into the government, the right-wing immediately launches a coup attempt. Troops of the Stahlhelm and Nazi SA enter Berlin and immediately begin clashing with our supporters! Reactionary officers within the Reichswehr have taken their troops out of the barracks and joined them with the Stahlhelm to stop us from taking power.

We manage to diffuse some of the hostility from the Reichswehr and the Stahlhelm, but fail to prevent the outbreak of fighting. We are forced to fight on the same side as the SPD, whether we want to or not.

- @civil_war: A civil war, then.

@far_right_braun
on-arrival: coup_progress += 2

President Braun faces a dilemma. Is it "democratic" to let democracy be destroyed, if the majority of voters have willed it so? Some, even on the left, suggest that the Nazis would not *truly* be as horrific as their platform suggests, and that giving them power would let them discredit themselves in the eyes of the public.

Alternatively, Braun could use the emergency powers of the presidency. Article 48 has been used by Hindenburg to promulgate anti-democratic and anti-worker policies; can Article 48 be used for good as well as evil?

#- @emergency_braun: We will form an emergency government with Braun's support.
- @new_elections: We will have new elections.
#- @far_right_win: Let the Nazis form their government.


@left_front
title: Is a United Left coalition possible?
subtitle: SPD + KPD [? if sapd_formed: + SAPD ?] ([+ left_front +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: SPD + KPD [? if sapd_formed: + SAPD ?] ([+ left_front +]%). [? if kpd_relation < 50 : We do not have adequate relations with the KPD. ?][? if communist_coalition < 3 : The Communists are too committed to their radical ways to partake in government. ?]
view-if: left_front >= 50
choose-if: (kpd_relation >= 50 or (kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators" and kpd_relation >= 40)) and communist_coalition >= 3

There are enough votes for a SPD + KPD coalition government, if such a thing were actually possible.

The far-right might attempt a coup, if such a coalition were formed.

- @left_front_impossible: This is impossible.
- @left_front_possible: This could be possible.

@left_front_impossible
go-to: coalition_menu

A far left coalition is impossible.


@left_front_possible

The KPD is still very reluctant to join a coalition, despite grassroots friendliness between our memberships. The Stalinist leadership is vehemently against such a thing. They demand the appointment of Ernst Thälmann as chancellor in exchange for a coalition. [? if president == "Hindenburg" : There is no chance whatsoever that President Hindenburg would approve of the appointment of a die-hard communist as chancellor. ?] Alternatively, if our relations with them are good enough, we could convince them to support the appointment of one of our centrist or left-leaning members as chancellor.

- @thalmann_chancellor: Appoint Thälmann as chancellor.
- @left_front_resources
- @left_front_relations
- @coalition_menu: Try a different governing arrangement.

@thalmann_chancellor
choose-if: president == "Braun" and reformist_strength + neorevisionist_strength < left_strength
unavailable-subtitle: [? if president != "Braun": President [+ president +] would never allow such a thing. ?] [? if reformist_strength >= left_strength : Most in the parliamentary party would not support Thälmann as chancellor. ?]
on-arrival: chancellor = "Thälmann"; chancellor_party = "KPD"; kpd_relation = 80; in_left_front = 1; spd_in_government = 1 

With great reluctance, President [+ president +] appoints [+ chancellor +] as chancellor.

Immediately, [+ chancellor +] goes to work building a "Soviet Germany": consolidating as much power as possible in the KPD, purging state institutions of anti-communists, and sending street fighters against the "enemies of the people".

In response to [+ chancellor +] being appointed Chancellor, the right-wing forces launches almost immediately launch an attempted coup. Troops of the Stahlhelm and Nazi SA enter Berlin and immediately begin clashing with our supporters! Reactionary officers within the Reichswehr have taken their troops out of the barracks and joined them with the Stahlhelm to stop the KPD from taking power. We are forced to be on the same side as the KPD, whether we want to or not.

- @civil_war


@left_front_resources
title: Use our resources to smooth things over.
unavailable-subtitle: Required: 3 resources
subtitle: -3 resources
choose-if: resources >= 3
on-arrival: resources -= 3
go-to: left_front_success

@left_front_relations
title: Convince the KPD to accept democracy.
unavailable-subtitle: Our relationships with the KPD are not good enough.
choose-if: kpd_relation >= 60 or kpd_party_leader == "Conciliators"
go-to: left_front_success


@left_front_success
on-arrival: spd_in_government = 1; in_left_front = 1; chancellor = "Breitscheid"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; coup_progress += 3; capital_strike_progress += 2; in_popular_front = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; kpd_relation += 10
go-to: left_front_civil_war if coup_progress >= 10; left_front_no_civil_war if coup_progress < 10
achievement: einheitsfront

Somehow, surprisingly, the left coalition is successfully formed, without appointing Thälmann as chancellor. The consensus choice for chancellor, accepted by the SPD, KPD, and President [+ president +], is Rudolf Breitscheid, who belongs to the centrist faction of the SPD, but was acceptable to the left due to his previous membership in the left-wing anti-war USPD.

# just raise the coup limit, don't immediately go to civil war

@left_front_no_civil_war
on-arrival: kpd_goals_seen = 0; foreign_minister_party = "SPD"; interior_minister_party = "SPD"; justice_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; finance_minister_party = "SPD"; agriculture_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.05

In response to the KPD's entrance into the government, the right-wing takes a "wait-and-see" approach for now. They expect that our government will be unstable and incompetent, and will collapse of its own accord, discrediting the left and eventually enabling the destruction of the Weimar Republic. Our task is to prove them wrong.

The KPD has taken an abstentionist position with regards to ministries. They claim to be participating as the "loyal opposition" in the worker's government, supporting us from the outside while also running their own propaganda campaigns to turn workers to their side. They seem to expect that we would inevitably fail, and that our failure would benefit them. 

Whatever their reasoning is, the SPD has control over the ministries of government.

@left_front_civil_war
on-arrival: reichswehr_loyalty += 0.1

In response to the KPD's entrance into the government, the right-wing immediately launches a coup attempt. Troops of the Stahlhelm and Nazi SA enter Berlin and begin clashing with our supporters. Reactionary officers within the Reichswehr have taken their troops out of the barracks and joined them with the Stahlhelm to stop us from taking power.

- @civil_war: A civil war, then.



@centre_right_coalition
title: We can form a Centre-right Coalition.
subtitle: <span style="color: #d9c640;">**LVP**</span> + <span style="color: #000;">**Z**</span> + <span style="color: #69A2be;">**BVP**</span> + <span style="color: #909090;">**Others**</span> + <span style="color: #598dca;">**DNVP**</span> ([+ centre_right_coalition +]%)
unavailable-subtitle: <span style="color: #d9c640;">**LVP**</span> + <span style="color: #000;">**Z**</span> + <span style="color: #69A2be;">**BVP**</span> + <span style="color: #909090;">**Others**</span> + <span style="color: #598dca;">**DNVP**</span> ([+ centre_right_coalition +]%) - [? if ((lvp_relation < 45 and lvp_ideology == "Left") or (lvp_relation < 35 and lvp_ideology == "Centre") or (lvp_relation < 25 and lvp_ideology == "Right")): We do not have good enough relations with the LVP. ?][? if ((dnvp_relation < 35 and dnvp_ideology == "Left") or (dnvp_relation < 45 and dnvp_ideology == "Centre") or (dnvp_relation < 60 and dnvp_ideology == "Right")): We do not have good enough relations with the DNVP. ?][? if ((left_strength*2 + center_strength >= clerical_strength + labour_strength) and dnvp_ideology == "Right"): The party has not debased itself enough to work with Hugenberg. ?][? if ((left_strength >= clerical_strength + labour_strength) and dnvp_ideology == "Centre"): The party is too left-wing for this. ?]
view_if: centre_right_coalition >= 50
choose-if: (((lvp_relation >= 45 and lvp_ideology == "Left") or (lvp_relation >= 35 and lvp_ideology == "Centre") or (lvp_relation >= 25 and lvp_ideology == "Right")) and ((dnvp_relation >= 35 and dnvp_ideology == "Left") or (dnvp_relation >= 45 and dnvp_ideology == "Centre" and (left_strength < clerical_strength + labour_strength)) or (dnvp_relation >= 60 and dnvp_ideology == "Right" and (left_strength*2 + center_strength < clerical_strength + labour_strength)))) 
on-arrival: in_centre_right_coalition = 1; lvp_in_government = 1; z_in_government = 1; dnvp_in_government = 1; in_popular_front = 0; in_weimar_coalition = 0; in_left_front = 0; in_united_front = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; foreign_minister_party = "LVP"; interior_minister_party = "DNVP"; justice_minister_party = "LVP"; labor_minister_party = "LVP"; reichswehr_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = "LVP"; finance_minister_party = "DNVP"; agriculture_minister_party = "DNVP"; foreign_minister = "Curtius"; interior_minister = "von Keudell"; justice_minister = "Kahl"; labor_minister = "Thiel"; reichswehr_minister = "Reinhardt"; economic_minister = "von Raumer"; finance_minister = "von Schlieben"; agriculture_minister = "Schiele";

There are enough votes for a centre-right coalition of the Center (+ BVP), LVP, DNVP, and minor conservative parties. 

- @marx
- @luther
- @hergt

@luther
title: Hans Luther for Chancellor
subtitle: Hans Luther is a LVP-aligned independent. Perhaps granting them the chancellery may increase our leverage?
on-arrival: chancellor = "Luther"; chancellor_party = "Independent"; lvp_relation += 5; leverage += 5; 

Hans Luther, former president of the Reichsbank, has been appointed chancellor. The LVP is pleased that someone aligned to them has been granted the chancellery.

- @ministries: We must select our ministries.

@hergt
title: Oskar Hergt for Chancellor
subtitle: A man of the DNVP in the Reichskanzlei? 
unavailable-subtitle: The DNVP is not strong enough to demand the chancellery.
on-arrival: chancellor = "Hergt"; chancellor_party = "DNVP"; lvp_relation -= 5; rdp_relation -= 12; uspd_relation -= 12; spd_relation -= 12; spd_coalition -= 4; leverage += 5; 
choose-if: dnvp_r >= (lvp_r + 2) and dnvp_r >= (z_r + 2)

Oskar Hergt of the DNVP Has been appointed Chancellor - a firm nationalist and monarchist, despite his relatively moderate reputation. The left is furious.

- @ministries: We must select our ministries.


@no_majority
title: There is no clear governing majority.
view-if: weimar_coalition < 50 and grand_coalition < 50 and popular_front_coalition < 50 and united_front_coalition < 50 and far_right_coalition < 50
on-arrival: no_majority_elections += 1
go-to: no_majority_spd if chancellor_party = "SPD" or chancellor == "Marx"

# TODO: if there is an anti-democratic coalition majority, you should appoint Papen.

# either new elections, or Hindenburg appoints either Brüning, Papen, Schleicher, or Hitler.

@no_majority_spd
on-arrival: chancellor = "Brüning"; chancellor_party = "Z"

There is no path to an obviously workable majority. Since President Hindenburg is unwilling to work with a minority or caretaker SPD government, his preferred chancellor is Heinrich Brüning of the Center Party, who could lead a "presidential" government.

#- @new_grand_coalition: We will try to form a new grand coalition.
- @new_elections: We will have new elections.

# - if NSDAP is the largest party and the 

@brauns_dilemma
title: There is no clear governing majority.
subtitle: President Braun faces a dilemma.
view-if: president == "Braun" and (grand_coalition < 50 or grand_coalition_failed == 1)

President Braun faces a dilemma. He desperately desires a socialist or at least democratic government, but the electoral results are not there for such. Article 48 has been used by Hindenburg to promulgate anti-democratic and anti-worker policies; can Article 48 be used for good as well as evil?

- @emergency_braun: We will form an emergency government with Braun's support.
- @new_elections: We will have new elections.
- @left_front
- @popular_front_coalition
#- @far_right_coalition

@emergency_braun
title: We will form an emergency government with Braun's support.
subtitle: This may have the effect of inflamming public sentiment against us, and the reactionaries will be against us each step of the way.
on-arrival: sa_strength += 100; sh_strength += 100; in_emergency_government = 1

Yes, an emergency minority government, with the support of the SPD. Who should lead this emergency minority government?

- @braun_emergency_chancellor: Otto Braun for Chancellor-President!
- @breitscheid_emergency_chancellor: Rudolf Breitscheid for emergency Chancellor.
- @bruning_emergency_chancellor: Brüning of the Center Party, as a goodwill gesture toward the bourgeoisie.
- @wirth_emergency_chancellor: Joseph Wirth of the Center Party, as a gesture of republican unity.

@braun_emergency_chancellor
subtitle: This is unprecedented.
view-if: not historical_mode or not spd_prussia
on-arrival: chancellor = "Braun"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; spd_in_government = 1; pro_republic -= 5; foreign_minister_party = "SPD"; interior_minister_party = "SPD"; justice_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; finance_minister_party = "SPD"; agriculture_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.1; 

Our experts have checked the constitution, and have discovered that there is no specific prohibition against the Chancellor also being the President (the President may not be a member of the Reichstag; there is no law saying that the Chancellor *must* be a member of the Reichstag).

Thus, we have Chancellor-President Otto Braun. He claims that he will resign as soon as the economic-political crisis is over. The right-wing parties, who were once clamoring to replace parliamentary rule with dictatorship or monarchy, are now clamoring for the restoration of democracy.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence: The Nazis immediately call a no-confidence vote against us...

@breitscheid_emergency_chancellor
subtitle: The Communists are warming to him...
on-arrival: chancellor = "Breitscheid"; chancellor_party = "SPD"; spd_in_government = 1; kpd_relation += 5; foreign_minister_party = "SPD"; interior_minister_party = "SPD"; justice_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; finance_minister_party = "SPD"; agriculture_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.1;

We have appointed Rudolf Breitscheid as emergency chancellor. The Communists consider him less objectionable than the alternatives, although it is unclear whether they will tolerate this government.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence


@bruning_emergency_chancellor
on-arrival: chancellor = "Brüning"; chancellor_party = "Z"; spd_in_government = 1; z_relation += 10; foreign_minister_party = "SPD"; interior_minister_party = "SPD"; justice_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; finance_minister_party = "SPD"; agriculture_minister_party = "SPD" 

The Center Party is pleased, and somewhat surprised, that we have appointed [+ chancellor +] as chancellor.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence

@wirth_emergency_chancellor
view-if: z_party_leader == "Joos"
on-arrival: chancellor = "Wirth"; chancellor_party = "Z"; spd_in_government = 1; z_relation += 10; foreign_minister_party = "SPD"; interior_minister_party = "SPD"; justice_minister_party = "SPD"; labor_minister_party = "SPD"; reichswehr_minister_party = "SPD"; economic_minister_party = "SPD"; finance_minister_party = "SPD"; agriculture_minister_party = "SPD" 

The Center Party is pleased that we have appointed [+ chancellor +] as chancellor.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence



@far_right_coup
title: The far-right parties immediately launch a military coup against us...
view-if: far_right_coalition >= 45
on-arrival: sh_strength += 150; sa_strength += 150; sh_militancy += 0.05; sa_militancy += 0.05

The far-right parties, seeing that we are willing to deny them government by questionably democratic means, have decided that they can only take power by undemocratic means, and have risen up in force against the sitting government.

Their numbers are bolstered by the many government workers who are against the prospect of a unified Socialist government. Police and soldiers defect to the SA and Stahlhelm.

- @civil_war: It is war.


@emergency_no_confidence
title: The Nazis immediately call a no-confidence vote against us...
view-if: far_right_coalition < 45
on-arrival: z_no_confidence = 1 if z_relation < 45; kpd_no_confidence = 1 if kpd_relation < 45; other_no_confidence = 1 if (z_relation + dvp_relation)/2 < 45; dvp_no_confidence = 1 if dvp_relation < 45; sa_strength += 200; sh_strength += 200; no_confidence_votes = nsdap_r + dnvp_r; no_confidence_votes += z_r if z_no_confidence; no_confidence_votes += dvp_r if dvp_no_confidence; no_confidence_votes += kpd_r if kpd_no_confidence; no_confidence_votes += other_r if other_no_confidence; no_confidence_succeeds = 1 if no_confidence_votes > 50

The NSDAP and DNVP will vote against us, of course. The other parties vote their conscience. [? if z_no_confidence: The Center Party is voting against us. ?] [? if kpd_no_confidence: The KPD votes against us. ?] [? if other_no_confidence: The assortment of minor parties are voting against us. ?]

In total, [+ no_confidence_votes +]% of the Reichstag is against us. [? if no_confidence_succeeds : We have lost the vote of no confidence. ?]

- @no_confidence_elections_new: There will be new elections, which we will try to delay.
- @no_confidence_win: We have won, for now.


@no_confidence_elections_new
on-arrival: {!
Q.in_emergency_government = 1;
Q.no_majority_elections += 1;
Q.next_election_month = Q.month + 6;
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 6;
if (Q.next_election_month > 12) {
    Q.next_election_month -= 12;
    Q.next_election_year = Q.year + 1;
} else {
    Q.next_election_year = Q.year;
}
Q.pro_republic -= 5;
Q.workers_spd -= 3;
Q.new_middle_spd -= 3;
Q.old_middle_spd -= 3;
Q.rural_spd -= 3;
Q.catholics_spd -= 3;
Q.workers_nsdap += 5;
Q.old_middle_nsdap += 3;
Q.new_middle_nsdap += 3;
Q.rural_nsdap += 3;
Q.unemployed_nsdap += 5;
if (Q.pro_republic < 45 && Q.pro_republic >= 38) {
    Q.workers_spd -= 6;
}
if (Q.pro_republic < 38) {
    Q.workers_spd *= 0.85;
    Q.new_middle_spd -= 5;
    Q.old_middle_spd -= 5;
    Q.rural_spd -= 5;
    Q.catholics_spd -= 3;
    Q.workers_nsdap += 5;
    Q.old_middle_nsdap += 5;
    Q.new_middle_nsdap += 5;
    Q.rural_nsdap += 5;
    Q.unemployed_nsdap += 5;   
}
!}
view-if: no_confidence_votes > 50

The next elections are set for [+ next_election_month : month +] [+ next_election_year +].


@no_confidence_win
view-if: no_confidence_votes <= 50
on-arrival: in_minority_government = 1; in_emergency_government = 0;
achievement: minderheitsregierung

We have won the vote of no confidence, and are currently ruling under an SPD minority government. Now our task is to fix the country.

